<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-07-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-07-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1078" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1078">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 831.415 A/31.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of
                                    Venezuela</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-07-06"><hi rend="italic">July 6,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>In the name of the people of Venezuela and in my own I thankfully
                            acknowledge the felicitations Your Excellency sends me on the occasion
                            of the celebration of the first centennial of our independence. Accept
                            my best wishes for the growing prosperity of the great American Nation
                            and Your Excellency’s personal happiness.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Juan Vicente
                            Gómez.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>